```julia
using Statistics

function weather_data_analyzer(temps)
    if isempty(temps)
        return (; average=nothing, max=nothing, min=nothing, trend=nothing) 
    end

    stats = (average=mean(temps), max=maximum(temps), min=minimum(temps))

    if stats.max == stats.min
        return (; average=stats.average, max=stats.max, min=stats.min, trend=:stable) 
    elseif stats.max > stats.min
        return (; average=stats.average, max=stats.max, min=stats.min, trend=:increasing) 
    else
        return (; average=stats.average, max=stats.max, min=stats.min, trend=:decreasing) 
    end
end
```
This function calculates the `mean`, `maximum` and `minimum` values for each day's temperature in the list `temps`. It then checks to see if all the temperatures are either all increasing, decreasing or stable (i.e., they have the same value). Based on this, it constructs a named tuple with appropriate values set as per requirement. If the list is empty, it returns a named tuple where all values are set to `nothing`.
